trans-unit.source: This overload is specific to parallelized queries.
trans-unit.target: 此重载是特定于并行化的查询。

trans-unit.source: A parallelized query may partition the data source sequence into several sub-sequences (partitions).
trans-unit.target: 并行化的查询可能分区成几个子序列 （分区） 的数据源序列。

trans-unit.source: The `updateAccumulatorFunc` is invoked on each element within partitions.
trans-unit.target: `updateAccumulatorFunc`对分区中的每个元素调用。

trans-unit.source: Each partition then yields a single accumulated result.
trans-unit.target: 然后，每个分区生成单个累积的结果。

trans-unit.source: The `combineAccumulatorsFunc` is then invoked on the results of each partition to yield a single element.
trans-unit.target: `combineAccumulatorsFunc`然后调用以生成单个元素的每个分区的结果。

trans-unit.source: This element is then transformed by the `resultSelector` function.
trans-unit.target: 此元素随后将转换`resultSelector`函数。

trans-unit.source: This overload of the Any method causes a fully-buffered merge to be performed before the result is returned.
trans-unit.target: 此重载的任何方法将导致完全缓冲合并之前返回的结果执行。

trans-unit.source: The merge behavior can impact performance or cause an out of memory exception in large enumerables.
trans-unit.target: 合并行为可以影响性能或内存不足异常导致较大的可枚举对象。

trans-unit.source: To avoid the merge behavior, use the overload of Any that takes a Func parameter, or else use an alternative method such as FirstOrDefault.
trans-unit.target: 若要避免合并行为，使用任何具有 Func 参数的重载，否则使用如 FirstOrDefault 一种替代方法。

trans-unit.source: Enables treatment of a data source as if it were ordered, overriding the default of unordered.
trans-unit.target: 启用将数据源视为“已经排序”的处理方法，重写默认的将数据源视为“未经排序”的处理方法。

trans-unit.source: AsOrdered may only be invoked on non-generic sequences returned by AsParallel, ParallelEnumerable.Range, and ParallelEnumerable.Repeat.
trans-unit.target: 只可以对由 AsParallel、ParallelEnumerable.Range 和 ParallelEnumerable.Repeat 返回的非泛型序列调用 AsOrdered。

trans-unit.source: The source sequence which will maintain the original ordering in the subsequent query operators.
trans-unit.target: 将要维护后续查询运算符中的原始排序的源序列。

trans-unit.source: A natural tension exists between performance and preserving order in parallel processing.
trans-unit.target: 性能和并保留并行处理过程中的顺序之间存在自然张力。

trans-unit.source: By default, a parallelized query behaves as if the ordering of the results is arbitrary unless AsOrdered is applied or there is an explicit OrderBy operator in the query.
trans-unit.target: 默认情况下，并行化的查询的行为方式好像结果的排序是任意的除非应用 AsOrdered 或在查询中没有显式的 OrderBy 运算符。

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Order Preservation in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md).
trans-unit.target: 有关详细信息，请参阅 [PLINQ 中的顺序保留](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md)。

trans-unit.source: Allows an intermediate query to be treated as if no ordering is implied among the elements.
trans-unit.target: 允许将中间查询视为元素之间未应用任何排序。

trans-unit.source: The source sequence with arbitrary order.
trans-unit.target: 具有任意顺序的源序列。

trans-unit.source: AsUnordered may provide performance benefits when ordering is not required in a portion of a query.
trans-unit.target: 中的查询部分不需要排序时，AsUnordered 可能提供性能优势。

trans-unit.source: By default, PLINQ treats an input sequence as unordered unless OrderBy or AsOrdered is specified.
trans-unit.target: 默认情况下，PLINQ 将输入的序列视为无序除非指定了 OrderBy 或 AsOrdered。

trans-unit.source: However, if ordering was turned on and is no longer needed, then AsUnordered can be used to turn it off in mid-query, and this may result in performance benefits.The AsUnordered operator itself does not shuffle the source sequence; it simply removes the ordering requirement for subsequent operators.
trans-unit.target: 但是，如果排序已开启，且不再需要然后 AsUnordered 可以用于在中间查询中，将其关闭，这可能会导致性能优势。AsUnordered 运算符本身随机源序列中; 不排列它将直接删除后续运算符的排序要求。

trans-unit.source: If the source is ordered, subsequent operators might keep that ordering if it is more efficient to do so.
trans-unit.target: 如果源进行排序，后续运算符可能会使该排序，如果更高效，若要这样做。

trans-unit.source: AsUnordered can be called anywhere in the query; it does not need to be called immediately after AsParallel.
trans-unit.target: 可以在查询; 中任何位置调用 AsUnordered它不需要在 AsParallel 之后立即调用。

trans-unit.source: For more information, see [Understanding Speedup in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/understanding-speedup-in-plinq.md) and [Order Preservation in PLINQ](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md).
trans-unit.target: 有关详细信息，请参阅[了解 PLINQ 中的加速](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/understanding-speedup-in-plinq.md)和[在 PLINQ 中的顺序保留](~/docs/standard/parallel-programming/order-preservation-in-plinq.md)。
